description: Borrowed from Latin plexus (“a twining, plaiting, braid”).

nouns.description: plexus (plural plexuses or plexus or plexi)

entries.meaning: (anatomy) A network of anastomosing or interwoven nerves, blood vessels, or lymphatic vessels.
examples: Hyponyms: brachial plexus, cardiac plexus, celiac plexus, choroid plexus, Exner's plexus, internal carotid plexus, pelvic plexus, solar plexus, venous plexus

definitionGroups.group: An interwoven combination of parts or elements in a structure or system.

entries.meaning: (mathematics) The system of equations required for the complete expression of the relations which exist between a set of quantities.
